I"—<p><strong>In short</strong></p>
<ul>
  <li>
    <p><strong>model.eval()</strong> will notify all your layers that you are in eval mode, that way, batchnorm or dropout layers will work in eval mode instead of training mode.</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p><strong>torch.no_grad()</strong> impacts the autograd engine and deactivate it. It will reduce memory usage and speed up computations but you wonâ€™t be able to backprop(which you donâ€™t want in an eval script).</p>
  </li>
</ul>

